Package: vrtility
Title: Efficient Raster Processing Pipelines Using GDAL Virtual Rasters
Version: 0.3.3
Authors@R: 
    person("Hugh", "Graham", , "hugh.graham@permianglobal.com", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0001-9451-5010"))
Description: Leverages 'GDAL' Virtual Raster (VRT) capabilities to build
    efficient raster processing pipelines for Earth Observation applications.
    Uses a modular design based on nested VRTs to enable complex image
    processing tasks including cloud masking, multi-temporal compositing
    (median, quantile, geometric, medoid), and time series filtering. Supports
    both Python/'NumPy' and 'GDAL' muparser-based pixel functions. Integrates
    with SpatioTemporal Asset Catalog (STAC) APIs for cloud-native workflows
    and uses 'mirai' for parallel processing. Powered by 'gdalraster'.
License: Apache License (>= 2)
